{"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Computes and stores baked lightmaps for fast global illumination."}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"LightmapGI","kind":"identifier"}]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" node is used to compute and store baked lightmaps. Lightmaps are used to provide high-quality indirect lighting with very little light leaking. "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" can also provide rough reflections using spherical harmonics if "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/directional","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" is enabled. Dynamic objects can receive indirect lighting thanks to ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"light probes","type":"text"}]},{"text":", which can be automatically placed by setting ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/generateProbesSubdiv","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" to a value other than .disabled. Additional lightmap probes can also be added by creating "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapProbe"},{"type":"text","text":" nodes. The downside is that lightmaps are fully static and cannot be baked in an exported project. Baking a "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI","type":"reference"},{"text":" node is also slower compared to ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VoxelGI","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Procedural generation:"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Lightmap baking functionality is only available in the editor. This means "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" is not suited to procedurally generated or user-built levels. For procedurally generated or user-built levels, use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VoxelGI","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" or SDFGI instead (see "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Environment\/sdfgiEnabled"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Performance:","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" provides the best possible run-time performance for global illumination. It is suitable for low-end hardware including integrated graphics and mobile devices."}]},{"name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Due to how lightmaps work, most properties only have a visible effect once lightmaps are baked again."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","style":"note"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Lightmap baking on "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CSGShape3D","type":"reference"},{"text":"s and ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PrimitiveMesh"},{"type":"text","text":"es is not supported, as these cannot store UV2 data required for baking."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If no custom lightmappers are installed, "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" can only be baked from devices that support the Forward+ or Mobile rendering backends."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note"}],"kind":"content"}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Instance Properties","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/bias","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/bounceIndirectEnergy","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/bounces","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/cameraAttributes","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/denoiserRange","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/denoiserStrength","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/directional","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/environmentCustomColor","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/environmentCustomEnergy","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/environmentCustomSky","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/environmentMode-swift.property","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/generateProbesSubdiv","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/interior","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/lightData","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/maxTextureSize","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/quality","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/texelScale","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/use